rComments: A very good professor teaching a fascinating course. Excellent class discussions, covers a range of angles and makes the student think. Participation is mandatory, but with the exception of the term paper (naturally tough), the assignments are quite straightforward and simple. Only problem is slight disorganization.
teacherRatingTags: ['Participation matters', 'Get ready to read', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: This professor is great. He is a pro at his field, his lectures are very intellectually stimulating. He's very clear and concise. Long readings though. And get ready to really analyze the readings. He is a tough grader. But you'll learn a lot. One of my favs.
Really good at leading discussion. Forces you to THINK and think HARD.

Not sure what the person before me is thinking. This is an interesting class, and  if you do the math, you can't lose that much by missing class. Besides, it's in the syllabus so you know what you're getting.

Not a good professor. His evaluations are: Lottery presentations (he picks names from a dollar store party bag), participation, policy memo, analytic presentation (basically an essay presentation) and lastly a research paper with an abstract and bibliography. You cannot skip a class, god forbid if you do because you might lose 10% for the lottery.
Very Clear and Concise Lectures. If you attend class, you will do well.
